The House Committee on Governmental Affairs offers the following substitute to HB 521:
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 36 of Title 36 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 annexation of territory, so as to provide for equal reporting requirements for annexations and
3 deannexations; to revise procedures related to the deannexation of certain properties; to
4 provide for related matters; to provide for an effective date; to repeal conflicting laws; and
5 for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Chapter 36 of Title 36 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to annexation of
9 territory, is amended by revising Code Section 36-36-3, relating to report identifying annexed
10 property, maps and surveys, technical assistance to municipalities, and preclearance, as
11 follows:
12 "36-36-3.
13 (a) The clerk, city attorney, or other person designated by the governing authority of any
14 municipality annexing or deannexing property shall file a report identifying any property
15 annexed or deannexed with the Department of Community Affairs, the Legislative and
16 Congressional Reapportionment Office of the General Assembly, and with the county
